<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-07-22T13:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-07-22T13:00:00-05:00" n="69" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d69">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">840.48/5012: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi>
                                    (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Winant</hi></persName>)
                                    <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-07-22T20:00:00+02:00">July 22, 1941—8
                                    p.m.</date><lb/>[Received July 22—4:05 p.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>3137. Regarding your 2703, July 21, 7 p.m., and in answer to last
                                paragraph, I made careful inquiries to make certain that studies
                                suggested would be strictly exploratory and that no position or
                                commitments <pb facs="0111" n="103" xml:id="pg_103"/> would be
                                notified without consultation with us. Also that we would be kept
                                currently informed. I very much approve the wording of the reply you
                                suggest be made to Mr. Eden and on confirmation from you will
                                transmit the same to him.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Winant</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>